House Resolution 256
By: Representative Bonner of the 73rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Barbara Jean Allen; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Barbara Jean Allen on February 6, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Barbara Jean Allen was born on April 23, 1932, in Atlanta, Georgia, a beloved
5 daughter of Reuben Clyde Redwine and Mary Belle McBride Redwine; and
6 WHEREAS, she began her distinguished education career as an elementary school teacher
7 before transitioning into school administration and serving as the principal of Fayette County
8 Elementary School, where she provided strong leadership until her retirement in 1989; and
9 WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, Barbara Jean Allen was an active member
10 of Inman United Methodist Church and a frequent visitor of Indian Springs Holiness
11 Campgrounds, where she hosted her immediate and extended family for ten sweltering days
12 every summer in worship of her Lord; and
